245–Overleden","1300":"1300","1245":"1245","1265":"1265","1330":"1330","1272":"1272","about 1300":"circa 1300","1370":"1370","before 1290":"vóór 1290","Tounge Sutherland Scotland":"Tounga, Mali","Strathnaver, Sutherland, Scotland":"Sutherland, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Gigha, Argyll, Scotland":"Gigha, Argyll, Schotland"},"en":{"1272–":"1272–Deceased","1272–Female":"1272–Deceased","1265–1330":"1265–1330","1300–1370":"1300–1370","1245–Male":"1245–Deceased","1300":"1300","1245":"1245","1265":"1265","1330":"1330","1272":"1272","about 1300":"about 1300","1370":"1370","before 1290":"before 1290","Tounge Sutherland Scotland":"Tounga, Mali","Strathnaver, Sutherland, Scotland":"Sutherland, Scotland, United Kingdom","Gigha, Argyll, Scotland":"Gigha, Argyll, Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"MacNeil","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Irish and Scottish:  see  McNeil  ."],"variants":[{"name":"McNeil","meanings":["Scottish and Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Néill</b>, a patronymic from the personal name <i>Niall</i> (genitive <i>Néill</i>), see   Neil   and also <i>Neilson</i>, which was sometimes substituted for <i>McNeil</i> in Lowland Scotland.","History: The Scottish Clan McNeil claims descent from the early Irish king Niall of the Nine Hostages (see   O'Neill  ), and the name is associated in particular with the island of Barra in the Hebrides, having been brought there from Ireland in 1049. Some members of this clan later migrated to Antrim and Derry in Ireland. A different Scottish Clan MacNeill (spelled with two l's) has a traditional ancestral home on the island of Gigha."]}]},{"name":"of","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Korean Kyong, Kyong Suk, Young, Chae, Chi Young, Hang, Kil, Rin, Sang Hun, Chang, Chong, Insoo, Kum, Sun Young, Yom, Young Hwan.  Cambodian Kiwan, Oeurn, Phoeun, Pich, Saroeuth, Seung, Sophath, Sophea, Yoeun, Phan, Son.  Indian Shanti, Harendra.","Indian (Uttar Pradesh): Brahmin name, from Sanskrit <i>om</i>, the Hindu sacred and mystic syllable uttered at the beginning of prayers.","Cambodian: written ឱម, corresponding to the exclamation of solemn affirmation, of Sanskrit origin (see 1 above), chanted by Buddhist monks."],"variants":[{"name":"Oum","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Southeast Asian Heang, Hye, Kam, Kan, Kheng, Khin, Kun, Sang, Sok, Phong, Yom, Yoo, Youn, Cuong, Phal, Samnang, Tin.  Cambodian Sokha, Chheang, Choeun, Moeun, Roeun, Sambath, Samoeun, Savuth, Soeun, Sopheap.","Cambodian: written អ៊ុំ, from a Khmer word denoting an elder sibling of one's parent (i.e. ‘uncle’ or ‘aunt’). Compare   Om   3 and   Um   2."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"MacNeil of Gigha was born in 1272, in Gigha, Argyll, Scotland as the daughter of Aodh Iye MacNeil of Gigha. She married Donald MacKay - Third Lord of Strathnaver, Chief of Mackay before 1290. They were the parents of at least 2 sons."},"et":{"1272–":"1272–Surnud","1272–Female":"1272–Surnud","1265–1330":"1265–1330","1300–1370":"1300–1370","1245–Male":"1245–Surnud","1300":"1300","1245":"1245","1265":"1265","1330":"1330","1272":"1272","about 1300":"umbes 1300","1370":"1370","before 1290":"enne 1290","Tounge Sutherland Scotland":"Tounga, Mali","Strathnaver, Sutherland, Scotland":"Sutherland, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Gigha, Argyll, Scotland":"Gigha, Argyll, Scotland"},"fi":{"1272–":"1272–Kuollut","1272–Female":"1272–Kuollut","1265–1330":"1265–1330","1300–1370":"1300–1370","1245–Male":"1245–Kuollut","1300":"1300","1245":"1245","1265":"1265","1330":"1330","1272":"1272","about 1300":"noin 1300","1370":"1370","before 1290":"ennen vuotta 1290","Tounge Sutherland Scotland":"Tounga, Mali","Strathnaver, Sutherland, Scotland":"Sutherland, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Gigha, Argyll, Scotland":"Gigha, Argyll, Scotland"},"fr":{"1272–":"1272–Décédée","1272–Female":"1272–Décé